cture. Since this exciton has a picosecond\nradiative lifetime at low temperature, comparable with the energy transfer\ntime, its low-temperature photoluminescence is only quenched by a factor of\n$3.3 \\pm 1$ and $4.4 \\pm 1$ in the presence of mono- and bilayer graphene,\nrespectively. Finally, while our bare MoSe$_2$ on hBN exhibits negligible\nvalley polarization at low temperature and under near-resonant excitation, we\nshow that interfacing MoSe$_2$ with graphene yields a single-line emitter with\ndegrees of valley polarization and coherence up to $\\sim 15\\,\\%$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Nov 2020 22:41:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 5 Feb 2021 13:18:53 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 11 Mar 2021 10:03:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-30"}
